source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: text
---
Show device I/O error statistics for all devices of a filesystem

Reads per-device counters for write, read, flush, corruption, and generation
errors. The path can be a mount point or a device belonging to the filesystem.

With --offline, reads stats directly from the on-disk device tree without
requiring a mounted filesystem.

Usage: stats [OPTIONS] <PATH>

Arguments:
  <PATH>
          Path to a mounted btrfs filesystem or a device/image file

Options:
  -c, --check
          Return a non-zero exit code if any error counter is greater than zero

  -z, --reset
          Print current values and then atomically reset all counters to zero

  -T
          Show stats in a tabular format with columns instead of per-device
          lines

      --offline
          Read stats from the on-disk device tree (no mount required)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
